# Universal and Tissue-Specific Archetypes of Tissue-Level Division of Labor

This repository contains the analysis code and computational pipeline used in the study:

**“Tissue-level division of labor is coordinated across organs through universal programs and context-specific adaptations”**

Yonassi et al. (2025)

## Repository structure

Each numbered directory is a step of the analysis pipeline:

```
01_Preprocessing/          # Data preprocessing and sampling
02_Archetype_Identification/  # ParTI archetype identification 
03_Tissue_Composition/     # Tissue composition 
04_Intercellular_Crosstalk/   # Ligand-receptor
05_spatial_ligand_receptor/   # Spatial ligand-receptor analysis
06_Archetype_Robustness/   # Archetype robustness
07_Cross_Species_Analysis/    # Human-mouse cross-species comparison
```

## Data and Analysis Outputs

The associated data and analysis outputs are available on Zenodo:

Yonassi, S., Goldenberg, N., Walfisch, A., Cohen, E., Shaer Tamar, E., & Adler, M. (2025). *Tissue-level division of labor is coordinated across organs through universal programs and context-specific adaptations: Analysis code and data* [Dataset]. Zenodo.

https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.17779083
